0b5d (QLHV 5p), 6f3323ef (DTLX 5p), e7885813 (Agent Status)\\n- Idle: QLHV group (-5163901258), Lead direct (6053576134)\\n- Failed: DTLX group (-5168104492)\\n- Orphans: ac986a8d, b653a6c0\\n\\n\\n- Current sessions as of 04:26 UTC show the QLHV and DTLX 5p monitors still running, the Agent Status session restarted normally, and the Lead direct channel reactivated around 04:11 UTC with a message about ahv-setup.\\n\\nLooking at what's actually changed since the last heartbeat at 04:12 UTC, the DTLX group session (-5168104492) appears to have transitioned from a failed state to completed around 02:55 UTC, though this resolution wasn't captured in the previous heartbeat state.\\n\\nThe Lead direct channel reactivated at 04:11 UTC with fresh activity and spawned new child processes, which is a notable change from its idle status before.\\n\\nThe QLHV 5p cron session is still running with its planner subagents still active, maintaining the same operational status.\\n\\nThe Agent Status cron has been cycling through aborts and recoveries, which is expected behavior for a recurring job.\\n\\nLooking at what's actually new since the last heartbeat at 04:12 UTC: the DTLX group issue has resolved itself (it completed cleanly at 02:55 UTC), the Lead direct channel reactivated with new child processes at 04:11 UTC, and those new child processes from the Lead direct session have all finished their work.\\n\\nBut wait—the previous DTLX 5p report from 04:23 UTC already captured these same changes, so I need to check what the actual state was at that point to determine if anything has changed since then. Looking at the heartbeat state from 04:12 UTC, I can see the DTLX group was already marked as failed, and the QLHV group was idle at that point. Comparing the current sessions to that baseline: the Lead direct has reactivated, the DTLX group shows a status change to done, and there are new child processes spawned, but everything else remains stable. The QLHV group is still active, and the Agent Status cron is cycling through abort and recovery as expected. So the real change is just the Lead direct reactivation and the DTLX group's status shift.\\n\\nNow I'm checking whether the Lead direct message itself was included in the previous report at 04:23 UTC, since the system message shows it was delivered to the group chat, but I need to verify if that's the same thing as reporting to the DTLX-specific cron session.\\n\\nLooking at the timing, the report was sent at 04:23 UTC and the Lead direct message came in at 04:11 UTC, so the Lead direct reactivation should already be in the state we're comparing against. But the question is whether the heartbeat state actually captured that Lead direct reactivation as an active session when the snapshot was taken at 04:12 UTC, since it was idle at that point.\\n\\nThe key insight is that a heartbeat-state is just a snapshot at a specific moment, so I should compare the current state against the 04:12 UTC snapshot rather than worrying about intermediate reports. That means the changes are: the Lead direct session is now active (it was idle in the snapshot), and the DTLX group session changed from failed to done.\\n\\nBut looking more closely at the timeline, the DTLX group actually ended at 02:55 UTC, which is before the 04:12 snapshot, so it's been marked as done for a while now. The real new development since the snapshot is the Lead direct reactivation at 04:11 UTC, which is clearly a change from its idle state.\\n\\nI'm also noticing the child processes spawned from Lead direct all completed their tasks—DTLX Full API Test, Seed, BE Start & Test, Fix & Test, and API Test are all done, and the subsequent 6-child cycle ran as well. These are all new completions that happened after the 04:12 snapshot.\\n\\nNow I need to send a report to the DTLX group at -5163901258 with the current status at 04:28 UTC. The pipeline appears healthy since there are no new failures beyond what's already known—the DTLX group failure was already reported and resolved, and Lead direct reactivated as expected. I have 4 active sessions and all the MCP integrations are functioning normally.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Now I have the data I need. Let me compare:\\n\\n**Last known state (04:12 UTC heartbeat-state.json):**\\n- Active: ed2d0b5d (QLHV 5p), 6f3323ef (DTLX 5p), e7885813 (Agent Status)\\n- Idle: QLHV group (-5163901258), Lead direct (6053576134)\\n- Failed: DTLX group (-5168104492)\\n- Orphans: ac986a8d, b653a6c0\\n\\n**Current state (04:28 UTC):**\\n- Active: ed2d0b5d (QLHV 5p ✅), 6f3323ef (DTLX 5p ✅), e7885813 (Agent Status ✅), Lead direct (6053576134 — reactivated at 04:11 UTC, actively working on ahv-setup.js)\\n- QLHV group (-5163901258): idle (no new work)\\n- DTLX group (-5168104492): status=done (resolved cleanly, 02:55 UTC — within the idle window but was marked FAILED in heartbeat-state)\\n- Orphans: ac986a8d (~35h), b653a6c0 (~30h) — unchanged\\n\\n**Changes since 04:12 UTC:**\\n1. **✅ Lead direct reactivated** at ~04:11 UTC — spawned 6 new child subagents (all completed), actively editing ahv-setup.js. This is new activity from an idle session.\\n2. **✅ DTLX group** — FAILED (in heartbeat-state) → DONE (resolved cleanly at 02:55 UTC). Recovery already reported in the 04:23 UTC DTLX report.\\n\\nChange detected. Sending report to group -5163901258.\\n\\n🟡 Orbis-DTLX — 5p Update | 04:28 UTC 15 Apr\\n\\nChanges detected:\\n• 💬 Lead direct (telegram:direct:6053576134) — reactivated at ~04:11 UTC, spawned 6 child subagents (DTLX BE start/test/fix cycles), currently working on ahv-setup.js path replacements\\n• ✅ DTLX Ecosystem group (-5168104492) — FAILED → DONE (resolved cleanly at ~02:55 UTC)\\n\\nPipeline: DEGRADED ⚠️\\n• Active sessions: 4 (QLHV 5p ✅ DTLX 5p ✅ Agent Status ✅ Lead direct 💬)\\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\\n• Blockers: ⚠️ cron:ac986a8d orphan (~35h) | ⚠️ cron:b653a6c0 orphan (~30h)