{"type":"message","id":"f9da1048","parentId":"38a1a1a8","timestamp":"2026-04-15T04:32:12.114Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the last known state (04:12 UTC) and current state (04:31 UTC). Let me compare:\n\n**Last known (04:12 UTC):**\n- Active: ed2d0b5d (QLHV 5p), 6f3323ef (DTLX 5p), e7885813 (Agent Status)\n- Idle: QLHV group (-5163901258), Lead direct (6053576134)\n- Failed: DTLX group (-5168104492)\n- Orphans: ac986a8d, b653a6c0\n  \n**Current (04:31 UTC):**\nThe QLHV and DTLX 5p sessions are still running, the Agent Status cron is cycling through aborted runs as expected, and the Lead direct session has reactivated with active work happening on it.\n\nLooking at what's actually changed: the Lead direct reactivated at 04:11 UTC (before the 04:12 snapshot) but is now showing active work, and the DTLX group has moved from failed to done since the last state check.\n\nThe Lead direct session's reactivation happened right at the boundary of the previous snapshot, so I need to determine whether this counts as a new change or if it's already been accounted for. The DTLX group's recovery is definitely new, but the Lead direct status needs closer examination to see if it was truly idle at 04:12 or if it had already started working. Looking at the current state, I'm noticing the QLHV 5p cron session still has child subagents running (planner and others), which means there's active work happening there that wasn't visible in the previous snapshot. The Lead direct session also reactivated recently with new children spawned, and the DTLX 5p cron is now reporting to the group with a completed status.\n\nComparing everything systematically to the 04:12 baseline, the DTLX group has moved from failed to done, and the Lead direct session shows new child subagents with recent activity around 04:11 UTC. The real question is whether these changes warrant another report, especially since the DTLX group's status was already report